[4] Worldwide update - Polio Eradication Initiative
Date: Thu 21 Feb 2013
Source: Polio Eradication Initiative [edited]
http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek.aspx


Global Polio Eradication Initiative update as of 12 Dec 2012
------------------------------------------------------------
Total cases
Year-to-date 2013 / Year-to-date 2012 / Total in 2012
Globally: 2 / 18 / 223
- in endemic countries: 2 / 17 / 217
- in non-endemic countries: 0 / 1 / 6

Case breakdown by country
Country: Year-to-date 2013 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total // Year-to-date 2012 WPV1 / WPV3 / W1W3 / Total // Total in 2012 / Date of most recent case
Pakistan: 2 / 0 / 0 / 2 // 10 / 0 / 1 / 11 // 58 / 26 Jan 2013
Afghanistan: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 4 / 0 / 0 / 4 // 37 / 20 Dec 2012
Nigeria: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 1 / 0 / 2 // 122 / 22 Dec 2012
Chad: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 5 / 14 Jun 2012
Niger: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 15 Nov 2012

Total: 2 / 0 / 0 / 2 // 16 / 1 / 1 / 18 // 223 // 14 Jan 2013
Total in endemic countries: 2 / 0 / 0 / 2 // 15 / 1 / 1 / 17 // 217
Total outbreak: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 // 1 / 0 / 0 / 1 // 6

*Data in WHO as of 21 Feb 2012 for 2012 data and 19 Feb 2013 for 2013 data

Afghanistan
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 37. The most recent case had onset of paralysis on [20 Dec 2012] (WPV1 from Nangarhar).
- 2 new cases of cVDPV2 were reported in the past week, bringing the total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 to 9, and one for 2013. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [22 Jan 2013] (from Hilmand). This is the 1st case reported in Afghanistan in 2013.
- SNIDs were held on [10-12 Feb 2013] using trivalent OPV in Helmand and Kandahar and using bivalent OPV elsewhere.

Nigeria
- One new WPV case was reported in the past week (WPV1 from Kano), bringing the total number of WPV cases for 2012 to 122. It is the most recent case in the country and had onset of paralysis on [22 Dec 2012] [Note the cases in the FCT have not been included in the current report - Mod.MPP]
- All states with recently-confirmed WPV cases have been covered by at least 2 large-scale SIAs.
- No new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 8. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [24 Nov 2012] (from Kebbi).

Pakistan
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2013 remains 2, and the total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 58. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [26 Jan 2013][note, the above table lists the most recent date of onset as 14 Jan 2013] (WPV1 from Khyber Pakhtunkhwa)
- No new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 16. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [14 Dec 2012] (from Balochistan).
- Response activities to the latest WPV cases from 2013 were conducted in parts of KP and in areas of Karachi.
- All provinces with recently-confirmed WPV or cVDPV cases have been covered by at least 2 large-scale SIAs, in response.
- The security situation continues to be monitored closely, in consultation with law enforcement agencies.

Chad
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV cases for 2012 remains 5. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on 14 June 2012 (WPV1 from Lac).
- No new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 12. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [20 Oct 2012] (from Wadi Fira).
- SIAs were conducted on [8-10 Feb 2013] using trivalent OPV.
- The next Technical Advisory Group (TAG) meeting is tentatively scheduled for early April [2013], to review impact of the ongoing emergency action plan.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. No WPV cases have been reported in 2012. The most recent WPV case had onset of paralysis on [20 Dec 2011] (WPV1 from Maniema).
- No new cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases for 2012 remains 17. The most recent cVDPV2 case had onset of paralysis on [4 Apr 2012] (from Katanga).
- SIAs will take place [20-22 Jun 2013] using trivalent OPV and [18-20 Jul 2013] using bivalent OPV.

Horn of Africa
- One new cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week, from Somalia, with onset of paralysis on [9 Jan 2013].
- This latest case is linked to a cVDPV2 outbreak ongoing in south-central Somalia since 2011 -- 9 cases were reported in 2011 and one case in 2012 (July). Additionally, in 2012 this outbreak spread across the border to Kenya, with 3 cases reported from Dadaab, in North Eastern Province between April and June 2012.
- In late 2012 and January 2013, access to populations is being achieved for the 1st time in 3 years in key areas of south-central Somalia, as a result of concerted local-access negotiations. An emergency action plan for south-central Somalia has been developed and is being implemented. At the same time, efforts are on-going to further boost population immunity levels in accessible, polio-free areas of Somalia, as well as in border areas of Kenya.
- However, confirmation of this most recent case underscores that the outbreak is ongoing and more outbreak response must be implemented.

West Africa
- No new WPV cases were reported in the past week. One WPV case was reported in the region in 2012, a WPV1 from Tahoua province in Niger with onset of paralysis on [15 Nov 2012]. This is the 1st case in the country since December 2011 and is related to virus originating in Nigeria.
- In Niger, outbreak response immunization activities were conducted [15-18 Jan 2013], in close coordination with Nigeria, and were followed by NIDs with trivalent OPV on [2-5 Feb 2013], again synchronized with Nigeria. Vaccinations also focused on reaching mobile populations associated with population movements from Mali, including in refugee camps. OPV continues to be added to broader humanitarian assistance efforts in the region, including in Mali, Mauritania, Burkina Faso and Niger.
- Multi-country campaigns are planned across West Africa in April and May 2013.
- SIAs in Central African Republic (CAR) originally scheduled for [8-10 Mar 2013] using trivalent OPV have been postponed until [22-28 Apr 2013] due to security concerns.

--
