[For a map of confirmed polio cases in the world attributable to wild poliovirus (WPV) infection, see http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring.aspx.

For a map showing WPV infected districts in the past 6 months, see http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek/Polioinfecteddistricts.aspx

Of note in looking at the above tables and reports is that the earlier mentioned case of WPV associated disease in the FCT of Nigeria is not included in the above report. Hence, the total number of confirmed WPV cases for this year [2013] should be 3. And, according to the totals of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type (cVDPV), there have been 2 cases confirmed this year [2013], one in Afghanistan and one in Somalia, both cases being due to infection with cVDPV2. In 2012, there were a total of 66 cases of polio attributable to cVDPV2 and 2 cases of polio attributable to cVDPV3 (For a table showing confirmed cases of polio due to infection with cVDPV by virus type, year and country, see http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek/Circulatingvaccinederivedpoliovirus.aspx). - Mod.MPP]
